1
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:44,259
[A Moment But Forever]

2
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:47,229
[Episode 13]

3
00:02:21,310 --> 00:02:22,710
Excuse me, you two.

4
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,000
How rude.

5
00:02:34,270 --> 00:02:35,590
They didn't even greet me.

6
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:55,700
I'm back.

7
00:02:57,270 --> 00:02:58,150
Thank you for your hard work.

8
00:02:58,310 --> 00:02:59,190
Why don't we invite them over

9
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,470
to have roast goose together?

10
00:03:01,530 --> 00:03:03,250
It wasn't really hard work.

11
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:06,070
I just couldn't buy any roast goose.

12
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:08,190
Couldn't get any?

13
00:03:08,950 --> 00:03:10,430
I bought a live goose.

14
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:12,190
Why don't we roast it ourselves?

15
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:13,670
How do we roast it?

16
00:03:14,790 --> 00:03:15,630
How to roast it?

17
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,460
Isn't it simple? We use fire to roast it.

18
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:19,460
Don't run!

19
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:21,390
Stop running!

20
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,590
Where are you running to?

21
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:25,710
Still running?

22
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:27,150
I thought you were really capable.

23
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:28,990
Didn't expect that you can't even catch a goose.

24
00:03:30,510 --> 00:03:31,550
Isn't this what you said?

25
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:33,240
A big goose tastes better when stewed whole.

26
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,120
If I hack it down,

27
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,590
won't it become dumpling filling,

28
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:36,670
with feathers and all?

29
00:03:36,670 --> 00:03:37,670
We can't eat that!

30
00:03:38,350 --> 00:03:39,990
Alright then, carry on.

31
00:03:41,070 --> 00:03:42,070
What are you doing?

32
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,510
Don't run!

33
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:44,680
I want to eat roast goose.

34
00:03:44,829 --> 00:03:46,350
Zi Fei is negotiating with it.

35
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:48,870
The goose is charging at you!

36
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:58,630
It scared me.

37
00:04:02,790 --> 00:04:03,790
Your legs have healed?

38
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:12,830
They really have healed.

39
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:18,589
You agreed I could leave or stay as you please.

40
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:20,550
You can't go back on your word.

41
00:04:29,130 --> 00:04:30,560
You're so despicable.

42
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:31,990
Just to catch a goose,

43
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:33,720
you even used the Divine Left Hand.

44
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,190
Its disadvantage is

45
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,260
it can't speak.

46
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:37,909
Otherwise, it would have cursed you already.

47
00:04:37,990 --> 00:04:38,710
Zi Fei has already

48
00:04:38,710 --> 00:04:39,909
negotiated with it.

49
00:04:39,909 --> 00:04:41,950
It's just that the goose didn't agree.

50
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:44,430
Can this even be negotiated?

51
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:47,060
When I was coming up the mountain earlier,

52
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:48,350
I met two scholars.

53
00:04:48,510 --> 00:04:49,230
I originally wanted to ask

54
00:04:49,230 --> 00:04:50,110
where to buy roast goose.

55
00:04:50,110 --> 00:04:50,710
But those two

56
00:04:50,710 --> 00:04:51,870
completely ignored me.

57
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:53,340
Oh, right.

58
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:54,740
Those two have already gone up the mountain.

59
00:04:54,740 --> 00:04:55,790
Did you see them?

60
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:00,600
I saw them.

61
00:05:01,350 --> 00:05:02,550
But they weren't living people.

62
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:03,430
Those were images

63
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:04,590
of what happened here before.

64
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,790
Images?

65
00:05:06,350 --> 00:05:07,750
On Baitou Mountain, there's a kind of

66
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,940
special restriction.

67
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:11,350
Whenever the mist spreads,

68
00:05:11,710 --> 00:05:13,500
it records fragments of images

69
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:14,830
from that time.

70
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:16,950
The images are suddenly released

71
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:18,470
when there's thunder and lightning.

72
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:21,620
People walking, lying down, laughing, and arguing…

73
00:05:21,790 --> 00:05:23,110
They're all lifelike.

74
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:24,360
What were those scholars

75
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,990
doing on Baitou Mountain?

76
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:27,560
Because this used to be

77
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,750
a very famous academy.

78
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:29,590
Those who came here

79
00:05:29,590 --> 00:05:31,060
were all students seeking knowledge.

80
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:34,470
How do you know all this so clearly?

81
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:36,230
I used to study here too.

82
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:37,420
I've been here

83
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,670
for 60 years.

84
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:39,990
How come I've never seen you before?

85
00:05:42,150 --> 00:05:42,990
That was

86
00:05:42,990 --> 00:05:44,430
a long time ago.

87
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,670
A long time ago?

88
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:48,870
How old are you?

89
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:04,390
Send this letter back to the clan.

90
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:05,750
Have Baili Xiang investigate

91
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:06,950
when Baitou Mountain ever had

92
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:07,950
such an academy,

93
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:08,910
who taught there,

94
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:10,360
and what students were educated there.

95
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:12,150
Will Baili Xiang listen to you?

96
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:13,750
He's eager

97
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:15,230
to do something for me now.

98
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:16,590
Just go ahead and send it back.

99
00:06:16,630 --> 00:06:18,430
Alright, that's easy. I'll take care of it.

100
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:34,070
Have we

101
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:35,430
known each other for a long time?

102
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:46,750
Sir, your tea.

103
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:47,470
Please enjoy.

104
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:48,190
Thank you.

105
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:08,350
This is the Juque Sword.

106
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:12,750
Yes.

107
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:14,420
Why did you have it?

108
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:17,000
I found it.

109
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:19,750
Why were you looking for it?

110
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:29,550
It has saved me many times over the years.

111
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:31,430
It's truly a fine sword.

112
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:33,179
But it's not as

113
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,390
powerful as you said.

114
00:08:35,070 --> 00:08:36,230
It's just sharp, that's all.

115
00:08:38,669 --> 00:08:39,750
Why are you giving it to me?

116
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:41,710
It was meant for you in the first place.

117
00:08:54,710 --> 00:08:55,840
Who are you really?

118
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:57,910
Sixty years ago,

119
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:02,000
at the foot of Guizang Mountain in Yaoguang County, Baicheng Prefecture,

120
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:04,580
I saw you for the first time.

121
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:12,430
I was 17 that year.

122
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:14,670
Thinking my saber skills were perfected,

123
00:09:14,830 --> 00:09:16,300
I left home to wander the martial world.

124
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:18,430
I was determined to find

125
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:19,790
an equally matched opponent.

126
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:22,510
Unexpectedly,

127
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,910
I was defeated by you in one move.

128
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:27,990
I was furious,

129
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,190
so I clung to you.

130
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:32,210
I was truly ignorant of my own limitations.

131
00:09:33,590 --> 00:09:34,750
This is really delicious.

132
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:35,470
Try some.

133
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:36,590
I'll try some.

134
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:42,600
Miss, your tea.

135
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,550
Enjoy.

136
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:48,950
Thank you.

137
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:56,590
Later, at the estate in Minzhou,

138
00:09:56,990 --> 00:09:58,190
I found you again.

139
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:00,510
You were injured,

140
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:01,870
lying on the riverbank.

141
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:04,670
It snowed heavily that day.

142
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:07,360
My saber was frozen cold.

143
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,030
But I saw you again.

144
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:15,870
I was very happy.

145
00:10:45,470 --> 00:10:46,150
I took you

146
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:47,550
to a nearby estate to recover.

147
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:49,630
You acknowledged my kindness

148
00:10:50,270 --> 00:10:52,710
and taught me saber techniques in your spare time.

149
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,950
Although you weren't talkative,

150
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:56,910
I was truly happy

151
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:58,960
during that time.

152
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,950
Your wounds healed day by day.

153
00:11:04,990 --> 00:11:06,190
I knew you would leave,

154
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:08,870
but I didn't expect it to be so soon.

155
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:20,310
I didn't know where to find you.

156
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:21,910
I didn't even know

157
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:22,840
your name.

158
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,270
I only knew about this sword.

159
00:11:25,830 --> 00:11:26,630
I knew

160
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,310
you needed to find this sword.

161
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:31,830
I went to many places

162
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:33,110
and searched for many years.

163
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:36,070
I finally found this sword.

164
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:38,710
But I didn't know

165
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:39,910
how to give it to you.

166
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:42,030
So I went to look for you again.

167
00:11:45,550 --> 00:11:46,830
Time flew by so fast.

168
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:49,240
When I saw you again,

169
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:52,260
more than 20 years had passed.

170
00:12:03,470 --> 00:12:04,550
Only then did I realize

171
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:07,350
that the one I liked was an immortal.

172
00:12:08,550 --> 00:12:09,510
No wonder he could

173
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,830
break through my saber technique with one sword strike.

174
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:12,550
No wonder his wounds

175
00:12:12,630 --> 00:12:14,190
healed so quickly.

176
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,990
It turned out he wasn't human.

177
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:22,150
It made sense.

178
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:25,440
It was such a simple thing,

179
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,110
yet it took me so many years

180
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:28,350
to understand.

181
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:30,790
I'm so stupid.

182
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:33,430
Why didn't you call out to me back then?

183
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:36,270
I've heard that the immortals of the Youhu Clan

184
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:37,470
have long lifespans.

185
00:12:38,070 --> 00:12:39,950
Even without practicing any immortal techniques,

186
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:41,140
they can easily

187
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:42,550
live for several hundred years.

188
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:44,540
You're in your prime, Sir.

189
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:46,710
You probably don't know

190
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,240
what aging is like.

191
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:52,710
It's like

192
00:12:54,070 --> 00:12:55,270
teeth falling out,

193
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:56,940
skin sagging,

194
00:12:57,950 --> 00:13:00,320
ears going deaf, eyes blurring, and back hunching,

195
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:04,350
gradually losing the sense of taste,

196
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:05,910
unable to distinguish near from far,

197
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:08,240
memory slowly fading.

198
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,310
and unable to lift a knife or hold a sword anymore.

199
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:13,390
Every breath will feel

200
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:15,030
like there's a huge rock

201
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,720
pressing on your chest.

202
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:20,150
Every moment, you can feel

203
00:13:20,150 --> 00:13:22,350
your body dying.

204
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:28,550
You don't know, do you?

205
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:30,550
This is aging.

206
00:13:31,390 --> 00:13:32,590
It's irreversible,

207
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,990
growing older day by day.

208
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:39,990
I know everyone is different.

209
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:42,310
The divine race rules the Six Realms,

210
00:13:43,310 --> 00:13:45,270
the War Demons are stronger than the Youhu Clan,

211
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:47,710
and the Youhu Clan lives longer than humans.

212
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:48,550
But we humans

213
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:49,990
are not entirely useless.

214
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,310
We are numerous

215
00:13:51,630 --> 00:13:52,750
and can reproduce more easily.

216
00:13:53,070 --> 00:13:53,830
We are intelligent

217
00:13:53,830 --> 00:13:54,980
with dexterous hands.

218
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:57,030
Compared to livestock and wild beasts,

219
00:13:57,070 --> 00:13:58,430
we are much stronger.

220
00:13:58,820 --> 00:14:00,030
Many humans

221
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:02,110
envy the divine race's longevity

222
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:04,710
and the immortal race's ability to fly and traverse the earth.

223
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:06,310
But I didn't.

224
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:08,550
I thought I was detached

225
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:10,060
and clear-headed,

226
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:12,630
but at that moment,

227
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:15,670
the moment I saw you again,

228
00:14:17,470 --> 00:14:18,390
I suddenly felt an overwhelming

229
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,430
hatred for myself.

230
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,910
I hated being human,

231
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,630
hated being so old and ugly,

232
00:14:25,830 --> 00:14:27,360
hated my foolish delusions,

233
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,430
and my overestimation of myself.

234
00:14:29,350 --> 00:14:31,110
Can you understand this feeling?

235
00:14:34,350 --> 00:14:35,550
I couldn't face you.

236
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:37,430
I didn't dare to face you,

237
00:14:38,430 --> 00:14:39,740
but I didn't want to leave either.

238
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:42,270
I found a town at the foot of the mountain

239
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:43,270
and settled down there.

240
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:45,710
It was next to Fangwai Mountain.

241
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:47,630
Occasionally, you would come down,

242
00:14:48,070 --> 00:14:49,430
sometimes alone,

243
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,790
sometimes with attendants.

244
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:53,110
I knew you were doing well.

245
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:54,510
Time passed,

246
00:14:54,510 --> 00:14:55,790
day by day.

247
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:57,950
You never changed,

248
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:58,900
but I...

249
00:14:59,990 --> 00:15:01,470
I was about to die.

250
00:15:00,420 --> 00:15:03,510
♫I gaze into your deep eyes♫

251
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:08,730
♫For whom do you take apart the word "love"?♫

252
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,910
Ten years ago, when my time was almost up,

253
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:09,670
I wanted to go home one last time.

254
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:12,510
On the way, I encountered heavy rain

255
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:14,230
♫Turning around, it's like a dream♫

256
00:15:13,070 --> 00:15:14,510
and found a temple

257
00:15:14,630 --> 00:15:15,620
to take shelter.

258
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:20,000
♫I have betrayed deep love♫

259
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,430
People say the gods have disappeared,

260
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:25,230
♫Heaving a long, helpless sigh♫

261
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:27,070
but when I saw

262
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:30,180
♫Time flies too rapidly♫

263
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:28,470
that statue of the goddess,

264
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:31,230
I felt she was alive.

265
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:33,550
So,

266
00:15:32,870 --> 00:15:36,230
♫Life is like a flying bird♫

267
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:35,950
I asked her a question.

268
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:42,550
♫Joining, scattering, no way back♫

269
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:38,320
The question

270
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:39,710
was…

271
00:15:40,350 --> 00:15:41,150
I asked her,

272
00:15:42,110 --> 00:15:43,630
"They say gods love all beings,

273
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:46,670
♫Unable to get what I yearn for, I sink in sadness♫

274
00:15:44,830 --> 00:15:46,710
but why aren't all beings equal?"

275
00:15:47,070 --> 00:15:48,120
Did she answer you?

276
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:52,170
♫When I brush past love, fate is set♫

277
00:15:48,830 --> 00:15:50,730
Yes, she did.

278
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:52,230
What did she say?

279
00:15:53,690 --> 00:15:56,080
♫I've used up my brush and ink♫

280
00:15:55,230 --> 00:15:56,150
She asked me...

281
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,830
♫I couldn't describe♫

282
00:15:58,270 --> 00:16:00,270
"Do you want to change all this?"

283
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:04,120
♫This lovesick path with you♫

284
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:06,340
♫After the farewell, where are you now?♫

285
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:09,270
♫Who do you spend your days with?♫

286
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:07,430
That beam of light

287
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:08,940
gradually enveloped me.

